;; vite-react-ssg@0.9.1-beta.1 declares peer vite@^2-^7 but we run Vite 8.
;; The combination is build-verified; without this flag CI's `npm ci`
;; hard-fails on ERESOLVE (this is what broke the Cloudflare Pages build).
;; Remove once vite-react-ssg publishes a Vite 8 peer range.
legacy-peer-deps=true


;; **Known dependency risk (accepted, monitored):** `
;; vite-react-ssg@0.9.1-beta.1` is a beta pin and declares a peer range
;; of `vite ≤7`, while the project runs **Vite 8**. The combination
;; is **build-verified** (renders all pages, lint clean),
;; but `npm ci`/`npm install` hard-fails on `ERESOLVE` without `legacy-peer-deps`.
;; This is pinned in **`.npmrc`** (`legacy-peer-deps=true`) so local + CI installs succeed.
;; **Remove the flag once `vite-react-ssg` publishes a Vite 8 peer range** (or a stable ≥1.0 release).
;; Node is pinned to **22** via `.node-version`.
